President and founder of the House Of Politics (HOP) nationwide, Alhaja Aminat Irawo, has called on the National Assembly to give post humours award for Alhaja Kudirat Abiola. Kudirat is the wife of Chief Moshood Kashimawo Abiola, the acclaimed winner of the June 12 1993 presidential election who was post-humously recognized by incumbent president Muhammadu Buhari by declaring June 12 as Democracy Day. Alhaja Irawo also called on the national assembly to officially henceforth refer to late Abiola as former President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. She said late Alhaja Kudirat Abiola should be recognised because she was fighting for the actualization of an election later acclaimed to be the freest and fairest ever conducted in the nation. “Former military administrator of Lagos state, Brigadier Buba Marwa invited the late Kudirat Abiola for a meeting at Alausa on the day she was killed along Oregun road on June 4, 1996. I advised her not to go but she insisted on attending the meeting with Marwa because she was ardent in her fight for the masses. She died for democracy. Alhaja Irawo said if Abiola had been allowed to rule the country then, poverty would have been eradicated in the country. She also called for compensation for the children of MKO Abiola, especially Mumuni who was about 5 years old then. She called on the National Assembly to put in place a bill that will enable to government to pay compensation to the late MKO. She expressed gratitude to President Buhari for recognizing Abiola, saying past administrations had promised such without fulfilling their promises.